The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 November is 94,686 (10,913.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 October, there were 4,748 new confirmed cases (547.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 October, there were 4,554 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (194 extra cases).
